    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/anndata-object-manipulation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SCANPY integrates the analysis possibilities of established R-based frameworks and provides them in a scalable and modular form. Specifically, SCANPY provides preprocessing comparable to SEURAT [10] and CELL RANGER [6], visualization through TSNE [11, 12], graph-drawing [13\u201315] and diffusion maps [11, 16, 17], clustering similar to PHENOGRAPH [18\u201320], identification of marker genes for clusters via differential expression tests and pseudotemporal ordering via diffusion pseudotime [21]",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Scanpy provides clustering, differential expression, and other analysis functions that integrate with AnnData, but does not explicitly name the specific function signatures (sc.tl.leiden, sc.tl.paga, sc.get.rank_genes_groups_df) or detail .obs/.uns slot mechanics in the provided passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
