      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Scanpy is a scalable toolkit for analyzing single-cell gene expression data. It includes methods for preprocessing, visualization, clustering, pseudotime and trajectory inference, differential expression testing, and simulation of gene regulatory networks. Its Python-based implementation efficiently deals with data sets of more than one million cells (https://github.com/theislab/Scanpy).",
      "asbval:note": "Scanpy is confirmed as a scientific software project with open-source code on GitHub. However, the paper does not describe Scanpy's CI workflow, Hatch usage, or pytest configuration. The card assumes Scanpy uses these tools, but the paper provides no such evidence.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ci-pipeline-reproducibility-verification",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Scanpy (Example scientific software project with reproducible CI workflow via Hatch and pytest)",
