    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/k-nearest-neighbor-graph-construction/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Along with SCANPY, we present ANNDATA, a generic class for handling annotated data matrices ( https://github.com/theislab/anndata ). ANNDATA\u2014which stores a data matrix with the most general annotations possible: annotations of observations (samples, cells) and variables (features, genes), and unstructured annotations.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms AnnData is the data structure used by Scanpy. Storage of graph data in obsm/obsp is implied by the description of flexible annotation storage, though not explicitly named.",
