    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/leiden-clustering-of-cells/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SCANPY integrates the analysis possibilities of established R-based frameworks and provides them in a scalable and modular form. Specifically, SCANPY provides preprocessing comparable to SEURAT [10] and CELL RANGER [6], visualization through TSNE [11, 12], graph-drawing [13\u201315] and diffusion maps [11, 16, 17], clustering similar to PHENOGRAPH [18\u201320]",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Scanpy performs clustering on graphs after dimensionality reduction (PCA, TSNE, diffusion maps) and uses AnnData objects. However, the specific algorithm is stated as 'similar to PHENOGRAPH' and the paper lists Louvain as a dependency, not Leiden. The functional workflow (dimensionality reduction \u2192 neighbor graph \u2192 clustering \u2192 cell type identification) is confirmed, but the specific Leiden algorithm is not named in provided passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "leiden-clustering-of-cells",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply the Leiden community detection algorithm to a k-nearest neighbor (kNN) graph of single-cell transcriptomes to partition cells into discrete clusters without requiring a priori specification of cluster number. This scalable method is used after dimensionality reduction and n",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:02:17.095179+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/leiden-clustering-of-cells/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SCANPY introduces a class for representing a graph of neighborhood relations among data points... Typically, SCANPY's tools reuse a once-computed, single graph representation of data and hence, avoid the use of different, potentially inconsistent, and computationally expensive representations of data.",
