    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/single-cell-rna-seq-normalization/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We regress out confounding variables, normalize, and identify highly variable genes. TSNE and graph-drawing (Fruchterman\u2013Reingold) visualizations show cell-type annotations obtained by comparisons with bulk expression. Cells are clustered using the Louvain algorithm.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes a workflow that includes normalization before identifying highly variable genes and before visualization/clustering, which aligns with the scope. However, the paper does not explicitly state the ordering or mandate that normalization must occur before dimensionality reduction.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "single-cell-rna-seq-normalization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill immediately after loading raw single-cell gene expression count matrices (AnnData objects) and before identifying highly variable genes or performing dimensionality reduction.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:04:16.145962+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/sparse-matrix-format-handling/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SCANPY's core relies on NUMPY, SCIPY, MATPLOTLIB, PANDAS, and H5PY... Parts of the toolkit rely on SCIKIT-LEARN, STATSMODELS, SEABORN, NETWORKX, IGRAPH, the TSNE package... SCANPY's Python-based implementation allows easy interfacing to advanced machine-learning packages such as TENSORFLOW for deep learning, LIMIX for linear mixed models, and GPY/GPFLOW for Gaussian processes.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Scanpy uses scipy and supports sparse matrices implicitly (via AnnData), but does not explicitly discuss dask.array or lazy evaluation for sparse matrix preservation. Paper states AnnData 'supports sparse data and allows HDF5-based backing of ANNDATA objects on disk' and 'allows operating on an ANNDATA object without fully loading it into memory\u2014the functionality is offered via ANNDATA's backed mode as opposed to its memory mode.' This supports sparse/lazy evaluation but does not name dask.array specifically.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "sparse-matrix-format-handling",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Maintain sparse matrix representations (scipy.sparse or dask.array formats) throughout preprocessing and analysis workflows to avoid forcing large single-cell gene expression matrices into dense memory.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:04:26.402594+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/sparse-matrix-format-handling/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SCANPY provides preprocessing comparable to SEURAT and CELL RANGER, visualization through TSNE, graph-drawing and diffusion maps, clustering similar to PHENOGRAPH, identification of marker genes for clusters via differential expression tests and pseudotemporal ordering via diffusion pseudotime",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Scanpy includes preprocessing, visualization, clustering, and differential expression testing. Specific function names (normalize_total, pca, filter_genes) are not mentioned verbatim, but the abstract and results section confirm preprocessing capabilities.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "sparse-matrix-format-handling",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Scanpy provides pp module preprocessing functions (normalize_total, pca, filter_genes, etc.) with sparse-aware implementations",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:04:26.402594+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/sparse-matrix-format-handling/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Along with SCANPY, we present ANNDATA, a generic class for handling annotated data matrices... ANNDATA is similar to R's EXPRESSIONSET, but supports sparse data and allows HDF5-based backing of ANNDATA objects on disk, a format independent of platform, framework, and language. This allows operating on an ANNDATA object without fully loading it into memory\u2014the functionality is offered via ANNDATA's backed mode as opposed to its memory mode.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms AnnData supports sparse data and HDF5-backed lazy I/O, but does not explicitly mention Dask array support. The 'backed mode' is described as an alternative to memory mode, but Dask is not named.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "sparse-matrix-format-handling",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "anndata defines the AnnData data structure that encapsulates X as sparse or Dask array; handles lazy I/O and matrix format preservation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:04:26.402594+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
