    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/trajectory-inference-preprocessing/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Scanpy is a scalable toolkit for analyzing single-cell gene expression data. It includes methods for preprocessing, visualization, clustering, pseudotime and trajectory inference... the reconstruction of branching developmental processes via diffusion pseudotime [21]",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Scanpy supports trajectory inference for developmental processes and uses AnnData format.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "trajectory-inference-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have raw or normalized single-cell RNA-seq expression data stored in an AnnData object (.h5ad format) and your analysis goal is to infer developmental or differentiation trajectories",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:05:08.473265+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/trajectory-inference-preprocessing/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SCANPY provides... clustering similar to PHENOGRAPH [18\u201320]... and pseudotemporal ordering via diffusion pseudotime [21]... Typically, SCANPY's tools reuse a once-computed, single graph representation of data",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms clustering and trajectory inference workflow, but does not specifically mention PAGA or partition-based graph abstraction by name in provided passages. The functional concept of cluster-level abstraction for trajectory methods is supported, but PAGA specifically is not named.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "trajectory-inference-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use it specifically when you need to move from individual cell resolution to cluster-level abstraction before running partition-based graph abstraction (PAGA) or other trajectory methods that operate on clustered data",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:05:08.473265+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/umap-embedding-visualization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "SCANPY provides preprocessing comparable to SEURAT [10] and CELL RANGER [6], visualization through TSNE [11, 12], graph-drawing [13\u201315] and diffusion maps [11, 16, 17], clustering similar to PHENOGRAPH [18\u201320], identification of marker genes for clusters via differential expression tests and pseudotemporal ordering via diffusion pseudotime [21]",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly mentions TSNE and diffusion maps for visualization, PCA for dimensionality reduction, and k-NN graph construction (neighborhood relations). However, UMAP is not mentioned anywhere in the paper. The paper uses t-SNE and diffusion maps as primary visualization methods, not UMAP.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "umap-embedding-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Compute and visualize a 2-D UMAP embedding of single-cell transcriptomic data after preprocessing and dimensionality reduction (PCA and k-NN graph construction)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:05:24.187137+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/umap-embedding-visualization/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Scanpy is a scalable toolkit for analyzing single-cell gene expression data. It includes methods for preprocessing, visualization, clustering, pseudotime and trajectory inference, differential expression testing, and simulation of gene regulatory networks.",
      "asbval:note": "Scanpy is confirmed as the core toolkit with visualization capabilities. However, the paper does not mention a tl.umap() function. Paper explicitly lists TSNE and diffusion maps as visualization methods, not UMAP. The toolkit does support the general workflow described, but not specifically UMAP.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "umap-embedding-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Scanpy (Core single-cell toolkit providing tl.umap() function and AnnData object container)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:05:24.187137+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/umap-embedding-visualization/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Along with Scanpy, we present AnnData, a generic class for handling annotated data matrices ( https://github.com/theislab/anndata ). AnnData\u2014which stores a data matrix with the most general annotations possible: annotations of observations (samples, cells) and variables (features, genes), and unstructured annotations.",
      "asbval:note": "AnnData is explicitly described as the data structure for storing annotated matrices with cell and gene annotations, consistent with the card's description.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13059-017-1382-0",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "umap-embedding-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "anndata (Data structure (AnnData) for storing gene expression matrices, embeddings (obsm), and metadata)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
